{"id":"fornication","term":"Fornication","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>In every form of it was sternly condemned by the Mosaic law (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 21:9\">Lev. 21:9</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 19:29\">19:29</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 22:20\">Deut. 22:20</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 22:21\">21</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:23\">23-29</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 23:18\">23:18</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Exodus 22:16\">Ex. 22:16</a>). (See ADULTERY.)</p>\n<p>But this word is more frequently used in a symbolical than in its ordinary sense. It frequently means a forsaking of God or a following after idols (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 1:2\">Isa. 1:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 2:20\">Jer. 2:20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ezekiel 16\">Ezek. 16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hosea 1:2\">Hos. 1:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Hosea 2:1\">2:1-5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 3:8\">Jer. 3:8</a>,<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jeremiah 3:9\">9</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Leviticus 21:9","Leviticus 19:29","Deuteronomy 22:20","Deuteronomy 22:21","Genesis 1:23","Genesis 23:18","Exodus 22:16","Isaiah 1:2","Jeremiah 2:20","Ezekiel 16","Hosea 1:2","Hosea 2:1","Jeremiah 3:8","Jeremiah 3:9"]}